Wash your hands and put on an apron. Weigh and measure all the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 5.Roll out the pastry onto a lightly floured surface and cut out four circles using a 8cm/3Â¼ in cutter. Line four holes in a muffin tin with the pastry circles.Spoon the lemon curd into the pastry cases.Melt the butter in a small saucepan and leave it to cool a little. Next add the oats, sugar and flour to the butter and mix with a fork, breaking it up into crumbs.Sprinkle the crumbs onto the top of the tarts. Place the muffin tin onto a baking tray and bake for 15-20 minutes. Serve with fresh raspberries or strawberries.